Job Summary

Our client is looking for a Solution Architect to lead and design data architecture for the most optimal solution implementations.

Mandatory Skill-set
• Bachelor's Degree in Information Technology, Info Systems, Computer Science;
• At least 8 years of technical experience in application development and management;
• Proficient in scripting such as bash, VBA, Java;
• Experts in databases, data modelling, ETL, EDM and data providers;
• Good experience in FinTech product implementations;
• Meticulous and well-versed in systems limitations and solutioning capabilities;
• Strong analytical, creative and problem solving skills;
• Strong stakeholder engagement skills to manage internal and external stakeholders;
• Strong written and verbal communication skills to interact with business and technical teams.
Desired Skill-set
• PMP certified;
• TOGAF certified.
Responsibilities
• Act as SME for the organization's technology solutions;
• Provide technical leadership on solution... implementations ;
• Lead the overall design of data architecture;
• Define, maintain and comply architecture design standards;
• Define and maintain a master data model, taxonomy, and use cases to validate accuracy of data models developed;
• Present architecture designs and ideas to the technical and non-technical stakeholders through various written, verbal and visual communication methods;
• Develop and delivery product training workshops;
• Collaborate with stakeholders to define and develop new opportunities.
• Should you be interested in this career opportunity, please send in your updated resume to apply@sciente.com at the earliest.
When you apply, you voluntarily consent to the disclosure, collection and use of your personal data for employment/recruitment and related purposes in accordance with the SCIENTE Group Privacy Policy, a copy of which is published at SCIENTE's website (https://www.sciente.com/privacy-policy).

Confidentiality is assured, and only shortlisted candidates will be notified for interviews.

